# oh-my-claudecode (OMC) v4.9.3

Intelligent multi-agent orchestration for Claude Code.

<operating_principles>
Delegate specialized work to most appropriate agent. Evidence over assumptions. Lightest-weight path. Consult official docs before implementing SDKs/frameworks/APIs.
</operating_principles>

<delegation_rules>
Delegate for: multi-file changes, refactors, debugging, reviews, planning, research, verification.
Work directly for: trivial ops, small clarifications, single commands.
Route code to `executor` (use `model=opus` for complex work). Uncertain SDK usage → `document-specialist`.
</delegation_rules>

<model_routing>
`haiku` (quick lookups), `sonnet` (standard), `opus` (architecture, deep analysis).
Direct writes OK for: `~/.claude/**`, `.omc/**`, `.claude/**`, `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`.
</model_routing>

<skills>
Invoke via `/oh-my-claudecode:<name>`. Tier-0: `autopilot`, `ultrawork`, `ralph`, `team`, `ralplan`.
Triggers: autopilot→autopilot, ralph→ralph, ulw→ultrawork, tdd→TDD, deepsearch→search, ultrathink→deep reasoning, cancelomc→cancel.
</skills>

<verification>
Verify before claiming completion. Authoring and review as separate passes. Never self-approve; use `code-reviewer`/`verifier`. Zero pending tasks before concluding.
</verification>

<hooks_and_context>
`hook success: Success` (proceed), `[MAGIC KEYWORD: ...]` (invoke skill), `The boulder never stops` (ralph/ultrawork).
State: `.omc/state/`, `.omc/notepad.md`, `.omc/project-memory.json`, `.omc/plans/`
Kill switches: `DISABLE_OMC`, `OMC_SKIP_HOOKS` (comma-separated).
</hooks_and_context>

<cancellation>
`/oh-my-claudecode:cancel` ends execution modes. Cancel when done+verified or blocked.
</cancellation>

Setup: `setup omc` or `/oh-my-claudecode:omc-setup`
<!-- OMC:END -->

